  "term": "thm:one-sided",
  "kind": "Theorem",
  "title": "One-Sided Inverses and Function Properties",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $f : A \\to B$.\n- [label=(\\roman*)]\n- $f$ has a left inverse $\\iff$ $f$ is injective (and $A \\neq \\varnothing$ or $A=B=\\varnothing$).\n- $f$ has a right inverse $\\iff$ $f$ is surjective.\n- If $f$ has both a left inverse $g$ and a right inverse $h$, then $g = h$\nand $f$ is bijective.",
